| 11 | HBase        | HBase is an open-source, distributed, column-oriented database management system (DBMS) that is designed to handle large volumes of data and provide high availability and fault tolerance. It is built on top of the Apache Hadoop project, which provides a framework for distributed computing. HBase is known for its ability to scale horizontally, with support for sharding and replication, making it ideal for large-scale deployments.                                                                                                                                                             | 2009 |
| 12 | Apache Hive  | Apache Hive is an open-source data warehouse software tool that allows users to query and analyze large datasets using SQL-like queries. It is built on top of Apache Hadoop, which provides a framework for distributed computing. Hive is designed to be easy to use, with a simple SQL-like syntax and a focus on performance. Hive is optimized for large-scale data processing, with support for distributed computing and fault tolerance.                                                                                                                                                             | 2007 |
| 15 | Apache Kafka | Apache Kafka is an open-source distributed event streaming platform that allows users to publish and subscribe to streams of events. It is designed to be highly scalable and fault-tolerant, making it ideal for large-scale deployments. Apache Kafka supports a wide range of programming languages, including Java, Python, and Scala, making it easy to integrate with existing applications. Apache Kafka is known for its ability to handle large volumes of data and perform complex computations in real-time, making it a popular choice for big data analytics and machine learning applications. | 2011 |
+----+--------------+--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+------+

